            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 469,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5013,
            "text": "And couches raised up.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 469,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5014,
            "text": "Indeed We formed them (the houris and all believing women),",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 469,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5015,
            "text": "and made them virgins,",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 469,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5016,
            "text": "chaste, loving companions of the same age",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 469,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5017,
            "text": "for the Companions of the Right",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 469,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5018,
            "text": "a multitude of the ancients,",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5019,
            "text": "and a multitude of the later people.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5020,
            "text": "As for the Companions of the Left",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5021,
            "text": "(they shall live) amid burning winds and boiling water,",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5022,
            "text": "in the shadow of a smoking blaze,",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5023,
            "text": "neither cool nor good.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5024,
            "text": "Before they lived at ease,",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5025,
            "text": "and persisted in the great sin",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5026,
            "text": "and constantly said: 'What, when we are dead and become dust and bones, shall we then be restored to life?",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5027,
            "text": "What, and our fathers, the ancients'",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5028,
            "text": "Say: 'Those of ancient times and those of later times",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5029,
            "text": "shall be gathered together to the appointed time on a known Day'",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 535,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5030,
            "text": "Then you went astray, you that belied,",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5031,
            "text": "you shall eat (the fruit) of the Tree of Zakkum.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5032,
            "text": "You shall fill your bellies with it,",
            "numberInSurah": 53,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5033,
            "text": "and drink boiling water on top of that,",
            "numberInSurah": 54,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5034,
            "text": "and you will drink as the lapping of thirsty camels.",
            "numberInSurah": 55,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5035,
            "text": "Such shall be your hospitality on the Day of Recompense.",
            "numberInSurah": 56,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5036,
            "text": "We created you, why will you not believe!",
            "numberInSurah": 57,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5037,
            "text": "Have you thought about what (sperm) you ejaculate?",
            "numberInSurah": 58,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5038,
            "text": "Did you create it, or are We the Creator?",
            "numberInSurah": 59,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5039,
            "text": "It was We who decreed death among you. We will not be surpassed",
            "numberInSurah": 60,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5040,
            "text": "that We will change you and cause you to grow again in a way you do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 61,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5041,
            "text": "You have surely known of the first creation. Why then, will you not remember!",
            "numberInSurah": 62,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5042,
            "text": "Ponder upon the soil you till,",
            "numberInSurah": 63,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5043,
            "text": "is it you that sow it, or are We the Sower?",
            "numberInSurah": 64,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5044,
            "text": "If We will, We would make it broken stubble and you would remain wondering,",
            "numberInSurah": 65,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5045,
            "text": "(Saying:) 'We are laden with debts!",
            "numberInSurah": 66,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5046,
            "text": "Rather, we have been prevented'",
            "numberInSurah": 67,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5047,
            "text": "Have you thought about the water you drink?",
            "numberInSurah": 68,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5048,
            "text": "Is it you that send it down from the clouds or We?",
            "numberInSurah": 69,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5049,
            "text": "If We will, We would make it bitter, why then do you not give thanks?",
            "numberInSurah": 70,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5050,
            "text": "Have you thought about the fire you kindle?",
            "numberInSurah": 71,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5051,
            "text": "Is it you that originated its tree, or are We the Originator?",
            "numberInSurah": 72,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5052,
            "text": "We have made it a reminder, and a blessing to the traveler.",
            "numberInSurah": 73,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5053,
            "text": "Then, exalt the Name of your Lord, the Great.",
            "numberInSurah": 74,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 470,
            "hizbQuarter": 214,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5054,
            "text": "I swear by the fallings of the stars",
            "numberInSurah": 75,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5055,
            "text": "and that is a mighty oath, if you but knew",
            "numberInSurah": 76,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 536,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5056,
            "text": "it is indeed a Glorious Koran,",
            "numberInSurah": 77,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5057,
            "text": "in a Book protected (from tampering)",
            "numberInSurah": 78,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5058,
            "text": "which none shall touch except the purified;",
            "numberInSurah": 79,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5059,
            "text": "a sending down from the Lord of all the Worlds.",
            "numberInSurah": 80,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5060,
            "text": "What, do you hold this discourse in disdain,",
            "numberInSurah": 81,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5061,
            "text": "do you make it your provision to belie it?",
            "numberInSurah": 82,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5062,
            "text": "Why, then, when the soul leaps up to the throat of the dying",
            "numberInSurah": 83,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5063,
            "text": "and you are watching at that time",
            "numberInSurah": 84,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5064,
            "text": "We are nearer to him than you, but you do not see",
            "numberInSurah": 85,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5065,
            "text": "why then, if you are not revived,",
            "numberInSurah": 86,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5066,
            "text": "do you not restore his soul, if you are truthful?",
            "numberInSurah": 87,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5067,
            "text": "If he is among the near",
            "numberInSurah": 88,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5068,
            "text": "there shall be calmness and ease, a Garden of Delight.",
            "numberInSurah": 89,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5069,
            "text": "If he is a Companion of the Right",
            "numberInSurah": 90,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5070,
            "text": "(he will be greeted with): 'Peace be upon you, Companion of the Right'",
            "numberInSurah": 91,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5071,
            "text": "But, if he is of those who belied, and went astray,",
            "numberInSurah": 92,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5072,
            "text": "there shall be a hospitality of boiling water,",
            "numberInSurah": 93,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5073,
            "text": "and a roasting in Hell.",
            "numberInSurah": 94,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5074,
            "text": "Indeed, this is the certain truth.",
            "numberInSurah": 95,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5075,
            "text": "So exalt the Name of your Lord, the Great.",
            "numberInSurah": 96,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 471,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 57,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحَدِيدِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Hadid",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Iron",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5076,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and earth exalt Allah. He is the Almighty, the Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5077,
            "text": "To Him belongs the Kingdom in the heavens and earth. It is He who revives and causes to die, and He has power over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5078,
            "text": "He is the First and the Last, the Clear and the Hidden. He has knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 537,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5079,
            "text": "He created the heavens and the earth in six days, and willed to the Throne. He knows what penetrates the earth and all that emerges from it; all that descends from heaven and all that ascends to it. He is with you wherever you are. Allah sees the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5080,
            "text": "To Him belongs the Kingdom of the heavens and the earth. To Him all matters shall return.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5081,
            "text": "He causes the night to enter into the day and the day to enter into the night. He has knowledge of the thoughts of the innermost of the chests.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5082,
            "text": "Believe in Allah and His Messenger and spend (in charity) of that which He has made you successors. Whosoever of you believes and spends shall have amighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5083,
            "text": "Why is it that you do not believe in Allah, when the Messenger calls on you to believe in your Lord, and He has made a covenant with you if you arebelievers?",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5084,
            "text": "It is He who sends down clear verses to His worshiper, so that He brings you out of the darkness into the light. Indeed, Allah is the Gentle, the Most Merciful to you.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5085,
            "text": "And why is it that you do not spend in the Way of Allah, when the inheritance of the heavens and earth belong to Allah alone? Those who spent before the victory and took part in the fighting are mightier in rank and are not equal to those who spent and fought thereafter. Yet, Allah has promised each a fine reward, and Allah is Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 472,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5086,
            "text": "Who will lend a generous loan to Allah? He will multiply it for him and he shall receive a generous wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 538,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5087,
            "text": "The Day (will surely come) when you shall see believing men and women with their light running before them on their right hands, (it will be said to them):'Glad tidings for you this Day. You shall live for ever in Gardens underneath which rivers flow! That is indeed the mighty triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5088,
            "text": "On that Day the hypocrites, both men and women, will say to the believers: 'Wait for us so that we can take from your light' But they will be answered: 'Go back and seek a light' And a wall with a door shall be between them. Inside it there is mercy, and outside will be the punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5089,
            "text": "They will call out to them, saying: 'Were we not with you' 'Yes' they will reply, 'but you tempted yourselves, you waited (for problems to befall thebelievers), and you doubted, and were deluded by your own fancies until the Command of Allah came, and the deluder (satan) deluded you concerning Allah.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5090,
            "text": "Today no ransom shall be accepted from you or from the unbelievers. Your shelter is the Fire, that is your sponsor, the worst arrival'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 215,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5091,
            "text": "Is it not time that the hearts of the believers be humbled to the Remembrance of Allah and the truth which He has sent down? They should not be like those who were given the Book before this, whose time became very long so that their hearts became hardened. Many of them were impious.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5092,
            "text": "Know that Allah revives the earth after it was dead. We have made plain to you the signs in order that you understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5093,
            "text": "Indeed, those who give in charity, be they men or women, and those who lend a good loan to Allah, shall be repaid in multiples. They shall receive agenerous wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 539,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5094,
            "text": "Those who believe in Allah and His Messengers are the sincere and the martyrs before their Lord, they shall have their reward and their light. But those that disbelieve and belied Our verses are the inhabitants of Gehenna (Hell).",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 473,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5095,
            "text": "Know that the life of this world is but play and an amusement, and adornment, and a cause for boasting among you, a rivalry for greater riches and children. It is like rain whose vegetation pleases the unbelievers, but then it withers and turns yellow, becoming broken stubble. In the Everlasting Life is a terrible punishment, forgiveness, and great pleasure from Allah. The life of this world is nothing except the joy of delusion.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5096,
            "text": "Therefore, race for forgiveness from your Lord, and for a Garden as wide as heaven and earth, prepared for those who believe in Allah and His Messengers. Such is the Favor of Allah; He gives it to whom He will. Allah is the Owner of great favor.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5097,
            "text": "No affliction can befall either the earth, or yourself, except that it is (written) in a Book before We created it. That is easy for Allah;",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5098,
            "text": "so that you will not be saddened for whatever does not come to you, nor be overjoyed in what has come to you. Allah does not love those who are proudand boastful",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5099,
            "text": "nor those who are mean, and encourage others to be mean. And he that turns away, (know) that Allah is Rich and Praised.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 540,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5100,
            "text": "We have sent Our Messengers with proofs, and sent them with the Book and the Scales, so that people might establish the Scale (of justice). We have sent down iron in which there is great might and diverse benefit for people, so that Allah knows those who help Him and His Messengers in the Unseen. Indeed, Allah is the Strong, the Almighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 474,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5101,
            "text": "We sent forth Noah and Abraham, and appointed the Prophethood and the Book to be given to their descendants. Some were guided, but many wereimpious.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5102,
            "text": "Following them We sent Our (other) Messengers, and We sent following in their footsteps, (Prophet) Jesus, the son of Mary and gave him the Gospel, and put tenderness and mercy in the hearts of his followers. As for monasticism, they invented it thereby seeking the pleasure of Allah. We did not write it for them, and they did not observe it as it should be observed. We gave to those of them who believed their wage, but many of them are impious.",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5103,
            "text": "Believers, fear Allah and believe in His Messenger (Prophet Muhammad), He will give you a double portion of His Mercy and He will make for you a light inwhich to walk, and forgive you; Allah is the Forgiver and the Most Merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5104,
            "text": "So that the People of the Book may know that they have no power over any of the favors of Allah; that the favors are in the Hand of Allah; He gives it towhom He will. The Favor of Allah is the Great.",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 27,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 541,
            "ruku": 475,
            "hizbQuarter": 216,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 58,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُجَادلَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Mujaadila",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Pleading Woman",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5105,
            "text": "Allah has heard the words of her that reasons with you (Prophet Muhammad) concerning her husband and made her complaint to Allah. Allah has heard both of you discussing with one another. Indeed, Allah is the Hearer, the Seer.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5106,
            "text": "Those of you who say to their wives, 'Be as my mother's back' indeed, they are not their mothers. Their mothers are only those who gave birth to them. Indeed they speak dishonorably and falsely. But Allah is the Pardoning, the Forgiving.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5107,
            "text": "Those who say to their wives, 'Be as my mother's back' then retract their words thereafter shall set a person free before they touch each other again. By that you are admonished. Allah is Aware of all that you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5108,
            "text": "He who is unable shall fast for two successive months before they touch one another. If he is unable to do this, let him feed sixty needy people that, so that you believe in Allah and His Messenger. Such are the bounds of Allah. There is a painful punishment awaiting the unbelievers.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5109,
            "text": "Those who oppose Allah and His Messenger shall be frustrated just as those before them were frustrated. We have sent down proofs and clear verses, and for the unbelievers, there is a humiliating punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5110,
            "text": "On the Day when Allah will raise them up all together He will inform them of what they did. Allah has taken count of it, although they have forgotten. Allah is Witness to all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 542,
            "ruku": 476,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5111,
            "text": "Have you not seen that Allah knows that which is in the heavens and the earth? There is no secret talk between three but He is the fourth of them; nor between five but He is the sixth of them; nor between fewer or more but He is with them wherever they are. Then, on the Day of Resurrection, He will inform them of what they have done. Surely, Allah has knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5112,
            "text": "Have you not seen those who were forbidden to talk in secrecy together? They return to that which they are forbidden and talk secretly together in sin andhatred, and in disobedience to the Messenger. Then, when they come to you they greet you with greetings with which Allah does not greet you, and they say within themselves: 'Why does Allah not punish us for what we say' Gehenna (Hell) suffices them, they shall be roasted, an evil arrival!",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5113,
            "text": "Believers, when you talk in secret do not talk together in sin and hatred, and disobedience towards the Messenger, but talk of piety and caution. Fear Allah before whom you shall be gathered.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5114,
            "text": "Talking together maliciously in secret is from satan, so that believers should sorrow, yet he can not harm them at all, except by the permission of Allah. In Allah let the believers put their trust.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5115,
            "text": "Believers, make room in your sitting places when it is asked of you, and Allah will make room for you. When you are asked to move, so move, and Allahwill raise up in ranks those who believed among you and those who have been given knowledge. Allah is Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 543,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5116,
            "text": "Believers, when you consult with the Messenger, present before your consultation a free will offering. That is best and purest for you. But if you lack themeans, Allah is the Forgiver and the Most Merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5117,
            "text": "Are you afraid to offer a freewill offering before your consultation? But if you do not, Allah will turn to you again, then establish the prayer and pay theobligatory charity, and be obedient to Allah and His Messenger. Allah is Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 477,
            "hizbQuarter": 217,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5118,
            "text": "Do you see those who have been guided by a nation that incurred the Wrath of Allah? They belong neither to you, nor to them, and knowingly they swear to lies.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5119,
            "text": "Allah has prepared for them a grievous punishment. Evil indeed is that which they have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5120,
            "text": "They have taken their oaths as a disguise and bar from the Way of Allah, so a humiliating punishment awaits them.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5121,
            "text": "Neither their wealth nor their children shall help them a thing against Allah. They are the inhabitants of the Fire, and there they shall live for ever.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5122,
            "text": "On the Day when Allah shall raise them all up, they will swear to Him as they now swear to you thinking that they are upon something. Indeed, they are the liars!",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5123,
            "text": "satan has mastered them and caused them to forget the Remembrance of Allah. Those are satan's party; and satan's party shall assuredly be the losers.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5124,
            "text": "Those who oppose Allah and His Messenger shall be among the humiliated.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5125,
            "text": "Allah has written: 'I will surely be the Victor, I and My Messengers' Surely, Allah is the Strong, the Almighty.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 544,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5126,
            "text": "You shall find no nation believing in Allah and the Last Day loving anyone that opposes Allah and His Messenger, even though they be their fathers, theirsons, their brothers, or their tribe. Those, He has written upon their hearts faith and strengthened them with a spirit from Him. He will admit them to the Gardensunderneath which rivers flow, where they shall live for ever. Allah is pleased with them and they are pleased with Him. They are the Party of Allah; and the Party ofAllah are the winners.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 478,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 59,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحَشۡرِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Hashr",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Exile",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5127,
            "text": "All that is in heavens and earth exalt Allah. He is the Almighty, the Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5128,
            "text": "It was He who expelled the unbelievers among the People of the Book from their homes into the first exile. You did not think that they would go out, and they thought their fortresses would protect them from Allah. But Allah came upon them from where they did not expect, casting terror into their hearts that their homes were destroyed by their own hands as well as by the hands of the believers. Therefore, take heed you that have eyes.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5129,
            "text": "Had it been that Allah had not decreed that they should be dispersed, He would have surely punished them in this world. And in the Everlasting Life thepunishment of the Fire awaits them,",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 545,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5130,
            "text": "because they broke their promise with Allah and His Messenger; and whosoever breaks their promise with Allah Allah is Stern in retribution.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5131,
            "text": "Whatever palmtree you cut down or left standing upon its roots, it is by the permission of Allah, so that He might humiliate the impious.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5132,
            "text": "And whatever spoils of war Allah has given to His Messenger from them, you hastened on neither horse nor camel against them, but Allah gives HisMessengers authority over whom He will. Allah is Powerful over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5133,
            "text": "The spoils of war taken from the villagers and given by Allah to His Messenger belong to Allah, His Messenger and the near kinsmen, the orphans, the needy and the destitute traveler, so that it is not something taken in turns by the rich among you. Whatever the Messenger gives you, accept it; and whatever he forbids you, abstain. And fear Allah; surely, Allah is Stern in retribution.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5134,
            "text": "(A share of the spoils shall also be given) to the poor emigrants who were expelled from their homes and their possessions, who seek the Favor and Pleasure of Allah, and help Allah and His Messenger. These are they that are truthful.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5135,
            "text": "And those before them who had made their dwelling in the abode (the City of Madinah), and because of their belief love those who have emigrated to them; they do not find any (envy) in their chests for what they have been given and prefer them above themselves, even though they themselves have a need. Whosoever is saved from the greed of his own soul, they are the ones who win.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 546,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5136,
            "text": "Those who came after them say: 'Forgive us our Lord, and forgive our brothers who were believers before us. Do not put in our hearts any spite towards those who believe. Lord, You are the Gentle, the Most Merciful'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 479,
            "hizbQuarter": 218,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5137,
            "text": "Have you not seen the hypocrites? They say to their brothers among the People of the Book who disbelieve, 'If they expel you, we will go with you. We willnever obey anyone against you. If they fight against you we will certainly help you' But Allah bears witness that they are, without doubt, liars.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5138,
            "text": "If they are expelled or fought against, they will not go with them, nor will they will help them. Indeed, if they helped them, they would turn their backs andthen they would not be helped.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5139,
            "text": "Their fear of you in their hearts is greater than their fear of Allah; that is because they are a people who do not understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5140,
            "text": "They will never fight against you all together except from fortified villages or from behind walls. Their courage is great among themselves; you think them to be united, yet their hearts are not united. That is because they are a people who have no sense.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5141,
            "text": "Just as those who, not long before, tasted the mischief of their actions, there awaits for them a painful punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5142,
            "text": "Like satan when he said to the human, 'Disbelieve'; then as soon as he disbelieved, he said, 'Indeed, I am innocent of you, surely, I fear Allah, the Lord of all the Worlds'",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 547,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5143,
            "text": "Their end shall be that they live for ever in the Fire. That is the recompense of the harmdoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 480,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5144,
            "text": "Believers, fear Allah. Let every soul look to what it has forwarded for the future, and fear Allah, for Allah is Aware of the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5145,
            "text": "Do not be like those who have forgotten Allah so that He has caused them to forget their souls. Those, they are the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5146,
            "text": "The inhabitants of the Fire and the inhabitants of Paradise are not equal. The inhabitants of Paradise shall be triumphant.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5147,
            "text": "Had We sent down this Koran upon a mountain, you would have seen it humble itself and split asunder for fear of Allah. Such are the parables we strike for people so that they will reflect.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5148,
            "text": "He is Allah, there is no god except He. He knows the Unseen and the Visible. He is the Merciful, the Most Merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5149,
            "text": "He is Allah, there is no god except He. He is the King, the Pure, the Peace, the Confirmer, the Watchful, the Almighty, the Compeller, the Sublime. Exalted is Allah, above all that they associate!",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5150,
            "text": "He is Allah, the Creator, the Originator, the Shaper. To Him belong the Most Beautiful Names. All that is in the heavens and earth exalt Him. He is theAlmighty, the Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 548,
            "ruku": 481,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 60,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُمۡتَحنَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Mumtahana",
        "englishNameTranslation": "She that is to be examined",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5151,
            "text": "Believers, do not take My enemy and your enemy for your guides, offering them love when they have disbelieved the truth that has come to you, who expelthe Messenger and yourselves because you believe in Allah, your Lord! If you go out to struggle in My way seeking My pleasure, but secretly love them, I know well what you conceal and what you reveal; whosoever of you does this will have gone astray from the Right Path.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5152,
            "text": "If they come upon you, they will be your enemies, and stretch out their hands and tongues to do evil to you. They wish that you would disbelieve.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5153,
            "text": "On the Day of Resurrection neither your blood relatives nor your children shall be of benefit to you. Allah will differentiate between you, and Allah sees thethings you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5154,
            "text": "You have a good example in Abraham and those with him. They said to their nation: 'We are quit of you, and that which you worship, other than Allah. We disbelieve you, enmity and hatred has shown itself between us for ever until you believe in Allah alone' Except that Abraham said to his father: 'Surely, I shall supplicate to ask for forgiveness for you although I have no power to do anything for you with Allah' ' Our Lord, in You we have put our trust; to You we turn, and to You is the arrival,",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5155,
            "text": "Our Lord, do not make us a temptation for the unbelievers and forgive us. Our Lord, You are the Almighty, the Wise'",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 549,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5156,
            "text": "In those there is a good example for whosoever hopes for Allah and the Last Day. Whosoever turns away, indeed, Allah is the Rich and the Praised.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 482,
            "hizbQuarter": 219,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5157,
            "text": "It may be that Allah establishes love between you and those with whom you are at enmity. Allah is the Powerful, Allah is the Forgiving and the Most Merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5158,
            "text": "Allah does not forbid you to be kind and to act justly to those who have neither made war on your Religion nor expelled you from your homes. Allah loves the just.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5159,
            "text": "But Allah only forbids you to be guided by those who have fought against you in your religion's cause and expelled you from your homes or have supportedothers in your expulsion. Whosoever takes them as guides are harmdoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5160,
            "text": "Believers, when believing women come to you as emigrants, test them. Allah best knows their belief. If you find them to be believers do not return them to the unbelievers; they are not permitted to the unbelievers, nor are the unbelievers permitted to them. But give back to the unbelievers what they have spent, and there is no fault in you to marry such women, provided you give them their dowries. Do not hold on to the ties with unbelieving women, ask what you have spent and let them ask what they have spent. Such is the Judgement of Allah; He judges between you; and Allah is the Knower, and the Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5161,
            "text": "If any of your wives desert you to be with the unbelievers and you retaliate, give those whose wives who have deserted the equivalent of what they have spent. And fear Allah in whom you believe.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 550,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5162,
            "text": "O Prophet, when believing women come to you and swear loyalty to you upon the condition that they will not associate anything with Allah, and will notsteal, nor commit adultery, nor slay their children, nor fabricate slander between their hands and their feet, nor disobey you in any honorable thing, supplicate to Allah for forgiveness for them, Allah is the Forgiving and the Most Merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5163,
            "text": "Believers, do not take as guides those who have incurred the Wrath of Allah and who despair of the Everlasting Life (to come), like the unbelieversdespaired of the inhabitants of the tombs (that they shall be resurrected).",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 483,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 61,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الصَّفِّ",
        "englishName": "As-Saff",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Ranks",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5164,
            "text": "All that is in the heavens and earth exalt Allah. He is the Almighty, the Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5165,
            "text": "Believers, why do you say what you never do?",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5166,
            "text": "It is most hateful to Allah that you should say that which you do not do.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5167,
            "text": "Allah loves those who fight in His Way lining up as if they were a stacked building.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5168,
            "text": "And when Moses, said to his nation: 'Why do you harm me, when you know that I am the Messenger of Allah sent to you' But when they swerved away Allah caused their hearts to swerve. Allah never guides impious people.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 551,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5169,
            "text": "And when (Prophet) Jesus, the son of Mary said: 'Children of Israel, I am sent to you by Allah to confirm the Torah that was before me, and to give news of a Messenger (Prophet Muhammad) who will come after me whose name shall be Ahmad' Yet when he came to them with clear proofs, they said: 'This is clearsorcery'",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5170,
            "text": "And who does greater evil than he who forges a lie against Allah, when he is being called to Islam? Allah does not guide the harmdoing people.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5171,
            "text": "They seek to extinguish the Light of Allah with their mouths; but Allah will complete His Light, much as the unbelievers dislike it.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5172,
            "text": "It is He who has sent His Messenger with guidance and the Religion of Truth, so that He raises it above all religions, much as the unbelievers dislike it.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 484,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5173,
            "text": "Believers! Shall I direct you to a commerce that will save you from a painful punishment?",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5174,
            "text": "You shall believe in Allah and His Messenger and struggle for His Way with your possessions and yourselves. That is better for you, if you but knew.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5175,
            "text": "He will forgive you your sins and admit you to Gardens underneath which rivers flow, and to fine dwelling places in the Gardens of Eden. That is the mightytriumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5176,
            "text": "And other things that you love, victory from Allah and an opening that is near. (O Prophet Muhammad) give glad tidings to the believers.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5177,
            "text": "Believers, be the helpers of Allah. When (Prophet) Jesus, the son of Mary said to the disciples: 'Who will be my helpers unto Allah' The disciples replied:'We will be the helpers of Allah' A party of the Children of Israel believed, and a party disbelieved. So, We supported those who believed against their enemy, and they overcame.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 552,
            "ruku": 485,
            "hizbQuarter": 220,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 62,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الجُمُعَةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Jumu'a",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Friday",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5178,
            "text": "All that is in heavens and earth exalt Allah, the King, the Pure, the Almighty, the Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5179,
            "text": "It is He who has raised among the illiterate (Arabs), a Messenger from themselves, to recite to them His verses, to purify them, and to teach them the Book and the Wisdom, though before that they were in clear error,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5180,
            "text": "together with others who have not as yet joined them. He is the Almighty, the Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5181,
            "text": "Such is the Favor of Allah; He gives it to whom He will, and Allah is of abounding favors.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5182,
            "text": "The likeness of those who were loaded with the Torah, but did not carry it, is like that of a donkey carrying books. Evil is the example of the people who have belied the verses of Allah. Allah does not guide the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5183,
            "text": "Say: 'O you who are Jews, if you claim that of all people, you alone are the guided by Allah, then long for death if you are truthful'",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5184,
            "text": "But, because of what their hands forwarded they will never long for it. Allah knows the harmdoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5185,
            "text": "Say: 'Death from which you flee is sure to reach you. Then you shall be returned to the Knower of the Unseen and the Visible, and He will tell you all that you have done'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 553,
            "ruku": 486,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5186,
            "text": "Believers, when you are called to prayer on the Day of the Congregation (Friday), hasten to the Remembrance of Allah and put your trading to oneside. That is the best for you, if you but knew.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 487,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5187,
            "text": "Then, when the prayer has ended, disperse in the land and seek the favor of Allah, and, remember Allah often, so that you prosper.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 487,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5188,
            "text": "Yet when they see some commerce or amusement they flock to it, leaving you standing. Say: 'That which is with Allah is better than the amusement and commerce. Allah is the Best of Providers'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 487,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 63,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُنَافِقُونَ",
        "englishName": "Al-Munaafiqoon",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Hypocrites",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5189,
            "text": "When the hypocrites come to you they say: 'We bear witness that you are the Messenger of Allah' Allah knows that you (Prophet Muhammad) are indeedHis Messenger, and Allah bears witness that the hypocrites are truly liars!",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5190,
            "text": "They have taken their oaths as a cover and barred others from the Path of Allah. Evil is what they have done.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5191,
            "text": "That is because they believed, then disbelieved, because of this a seal has been set upon their hearts so they are unable to understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 221,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5192,
            "text": "When you see them their bodies please you, but when they speak and you listen to their sayings, they are like proppedup timber. Every shout (they hear) they take it to be against them. They are the enemy be wary of them. Allah kills them! How perverse they are!",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 554,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5193,
            "text": "When it is said to them: 'Come, the Messenger of Allah will ask forgiveness for you' they turn their heads in pride and you see them go away.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5194,
            "text": "It is equal for them whether you ask for their forgiveness or you do not ask for their forgiveness, Allah will not forgive them. Allah does not guide the evildoers.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5195,
            "text": "It is they that say: 'Spend nothing on those who follow the Messenger of Allah until they disperse' Yet to Allah belong the treasuries of heavens and the earth, but the hypocrites do not understand.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5196,
            "text": "They say: 'If we return to the City, the strong will expel the humiliated' But the might belongs to Allah, and His Messenger and the believers, but thehypocrites do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 488,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5197,
            "text": "Believers, do not let either your possessions or your children divert you from the Remembrance of Allah. Those who do that shall be the losers.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 489,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5198,
            "text": "So spend of that with which We have provided you before death comes upon any of you and he then says: 'O my Lord, if only You would defer me to anear term, so that I could give in charity and be among the good doers'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 489,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5199,
            "text": "But Allah will never defer any soul when its term comes. Allah is Aware of what you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 555,
            "ruku": 489,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 64,
        "name": "سُورَةُ التَّغَابُنِ",
        "englishName": "At-Taghaabun",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Mutual Disillusion",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5200,
            "text": "All that is in heavens and earth exalt Allah. His is the Kingdom, and His the Praise. He is powerful over all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5201,
            "text": "It is He who created you. Amongst you is an unbeliever and amongst you is a believer. Allah sees the things you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5202,
            "text": "He created the heavens and the earth in truth and He shaped you and gave you good shapes. To Him is the arrival.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5203,
            "text": "He knows whatever is in the heavens and the earth and He knows all what you conceal and what you reveal. Allah knows the innermost of the chests.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5204,
            "text": "Have you not heard the news of those before you who disbelieved? They tasted the mischief of their action, and for them is a painful punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5205,
            "text": "That is because, when their Messengers came to them with clear proofs they said: 'Shall humans be our guides' They disbelieved and turned away, but Allah was not in need (of them). Allah is the Rich and the Praised.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5206,
            "text": "The unbelievers think that they will never be raised up. Say: 'By my Lord, yes indeed, you shall assuredly be raised up! Then you shall be told of all that you have done. That is easy for Allah'",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5207,
            "text": "Believe in Allah, and His Messenger, and in the Light which We have sent down. Allah is Aware of all that you do.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5208,
            "text": "The Day on which He will gather you for the Day of Gathering; that is the Day of Loss and Gain. He who believes in Allah and does good deeds, Allah willacquit him of his evil deeds and admit him to Gardens underneath which rivers flow, where he shall live for ever. That is the mighty triumph.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 556,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5209,
            "text": "As for those who disbelieved and belied Our verses, they shall be the inhabitants of the Fire and shall live therein for ever. Evil shall be their arrival.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 490,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5210,
            "text": "No affliction falls except by the permission of Allah. For those who believe in Allah, Allah will guide his heart. Allah has knowledge of all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5211,
            "text": "Obey Allah and obey the Messenger. But, if you turn away, Our Messenger's duty is only to deliver the Clear Message.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5212,
            "text": "Allah, there is no god except He. In Allah let the believers put their trust.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5213,
            "text": "Believers, some of your wives and children are enemies; so beware of them. But if you pardon, overlook and forgive them, then Allah is the Forgiving, the Most Merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5214,
            "text": "Your wealth and children are but a trial, and with Allah is a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5215,
            "text": "Therefore fear Allah as much as you can, and listen, obey, and spend well for yourselves. And whosoever is saved from the greed of his own soul; those are the winners.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5216,
            "text": "If you lend a good loan to Allah He will multiply it for you and will forgive you. Allah is the Thankful, the Clement.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5217,
            "text": "He is the Knower of the Unseen and the Visible, the Almighty, the Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 557,
            "ruku": 491,
            "hizbQuarter": 222,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 65,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الطَّلَاقِ",
        "englishName": "At-Talaaq",
        "englishNameTranslation": "Divorce",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5218,
            "text": "O (nation of the) Prophet, if you divorce your wives, divorce them after (the end of their) menstrual cycle. Count their waiting period and fear Allah your Lord. Do not drive them from their homes or let them go away unless they commit a proven immorality. Such are the bounds set by Allah, he that exceeds the bounds of Allah wrongs himself. You do not know, perhaps after that Allah will bring a new event.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5219,
            "text": "When they have reached their term, either keep them honorably or part from them honorably. Call two honest men among you to witness and give yourwitnessing before Allah. Whoever believes in Allah and the Last Day is warned to do this. Whosoever fears Allah, He will appoint for him a way out,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5220,
            "text": "and provide for him from where he does not expect, Allah is Sufficient for whosoever puts his trust in Him. Indeed, Allah brings about whatever He decrees. Allah has set a measure for all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5221,
            "text": "As for your women who have despaired of further menstruating, if you are in doubt, then their waiting period is three months as well as those who have not yet menstruated. As for those who are pregnant, their term shall be the time they deliver their burden. Allah will ease (matters) by His order for whosoever fears Him.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5222,
            "text": "Such is the command of Allah that He has sent down to you. Whosoever fears Allah shall be relieved of his sins and given a mighty wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 558,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5223,
            "text": "Lodge them in your home according to your means. Do not harass them so as to (make life) difficult for them. If they are with child, spend upon them until they deliver their burden; and if they suckle give them their wage and consult together honorably. But if you both make difficulties, let another woman suckle for him.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5224,
            "text": "Let the rich spend according to his wealth and for he whose provision is little, let him spend from what Allah has given him. Allah does not charge a soulexcept with that He has given him. Surely, Allah will bring ease after difficulty.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 492,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5225,
            "text": "How many a village has turned in its pride against the Order of their Lord and His Messengers! We made it a stern reckoning, and punished it with a horrible punishment.",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5226,
            "text": "So it tasted the mischief of its action, and the end of its matter was loss.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5227,
            "text": "Allah has prepared a severe punishment for them. So those possessing understanding fear Allah. Believers, Allah has sent this down for you as a Reminder,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5228,
            "text": "a Messenger reciting to you the verses, clear verses of Allah, so that he may bring forth those who believe and do good deeds from the darkness into thelight. Whosoever believes in Allah and does good deeds He will admit to Gardens underneath which rivers flow where they shall live for ever and ever. For those, Allah has made a goodly provision.",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5229,
            "text": "It is Allah who has created the seven heavens, and of the earth their like, and the Command descends between them so that you know Allah is powerful over all things, and that Allah encompasses everything in knowledge.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 559,
            "ruku": 493,
            "hizbQuarter": 223,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 66,
        "name": "سُورَةُ التَّحۡرِيمِ",
        "englishName": "At-Tahrim",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Prohibition",
        "revelationType": "Medinan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5230,
            "text": "O Prophet, why do you forbid that which Allah has made lawful to you. Do you seek to please your wives' Allah is the Forgiving, the Most Merciful.",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5231,
            "text": "Allah has absolved you from your oaths. Allah is your Guardian, the Knowing, the Wise.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5232,
            "text": "The Prophet confided a certain matter to one of his wives but thereafter she disclosed it, then Allah revealed what she had done to him. He made part of it known and another part not. And when he acquainted her with it, she said: 'Who has told you this' He replied: 'I was told of it by the Knower, the Aware'",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5233,
            "text": "If both of you (wives) turn to Allah in repentance, even though your hearts inclined; but if you support one another against him, (know that) Allah is hisGuardian, and Gabriel, and the righteous among the believers; and thereafter the angels are his reinforcers.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5234,
            "text": "It may be that if he divorces you his Lord will give him in your place better wives than yourselves, women who have surrendered, believing, obedient, penitent worshippers and given to fasting; who were (previously) married, and virgins too.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5235,
            "text": "Believers, guard yourselves and your families against the Fire the fuel of which is people and stones, over which there are harsh, and stern angels who never disobey Allah in that which He orders and do what they are ordered.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5236,
            "text": "Unbelievers, make no excuse for yourselves this Day. You shall be recompensed only according to your deeds.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 560,
            "ruku": 494,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5237,
            "text": "Believers, turn to Allah in sincere repentance. Your Lord may acquit you of your sins, and admit you to Gardens underneath which rivers flow on a Day whenAllah will not degrade the Prophet and those who believe with him. Their light will run before them and on their right hands, and they will say: 'Our Lord, completeour light for us and forgive us. Surely, You have power over all things'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5238,
            "text": "O Prophet, struggle with the unbelievers and the hypocrites and deal harshly with them. Gehenna (Hell) shall be their refuge, an evil arrival!",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5239,
            "text": "Allah has given as an example for the unbelievers, the wife of Noah and the wife of Lot. They were married to two of Our righteous worshipers, but theybetrayed them. It was not for (Noah and Lot) to avail them a thing. It was said to them both: 'Enter the Fire with those who shall enter'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5240,
            "text": "But to those who believe Allah has given as an example Pharaoh's wife, who said: 'My Lord, build me a house before You in Paradise and save me fromPharaoh and his work, and save me from a harmdoing nation'",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5241,
            "text": "And, Mary, 'Imran's daughter, who guarded her chastity so We breathed into her of Our Spirit (Gabriel); and she put her trust in the Words of her Lord andHis Books, and was among the devout.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 28,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 561,
            "ruku": 495,
            "hizbQuarter": 224,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 67,
        "name": "سُورَةُ المُلۡكِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Mulk",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Sovereignty",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5242,
            "text": "Blessed be He in whose Hand is the Kingdom, He is powerful over all things,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5243,
            "text": "who created death and life that He might examine which of you is best in deeds, and He is the Almighty, the Forgiving,",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5244,
            "text": "who created the seven heavens, one above the other. You cannot see any inconsistency in the creation of the Merciful. Return your gaze, do you see anycrack!",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5245,
            "text": "Then return your gaze once more and yet again, your gaze comes back to you dazzled, and tired.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5246,
            "text": "We have adorned the lower heaven with lamps, and We made them a stoning for the satans, We have prepared the punishment of the Blaze for them.",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5247,
            "text": "And for those who disbelieve in their Lord there awaits the punishment of Gehenna (Hell) an evil arrival!",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5248,
            "text": "When they are cast into it they shall hear it sighing, while it boils",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5249,
            "text": "nearly bursting apart out of rage. Every time a host is cast therein, its keepers will ask them: 'Did no one come to warn you'",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5250,
            "text": "'Yes, indeed' they will reply, 'but we belied the Warner (Messenger) saying: 'Allah has not sent down anything, you are but in great error'",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5251,
            "text": "And they will then say: 'If only we had listened and understood we should not now be among the inhabitants of the Blaze'",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5252,
            "text": "So it is that they confess their sins. Curse the inhabitants of the Blaze!",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5253,
            "text": "But those who fear their Lord in the Unseen, for them there is forgiveness and a great wage.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 562,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5254,
            "text": "(Whether you) speak in secret or aloud, He knows the innermost of the chests.",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5255,
            "text": "Shall He who has created (all things) not know? He is the Subtle, the Aware.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 496,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5256,
            "text": "It is He who has made the earth submissive to you. Walk about in its land and eat of His provision. To Him is the Resurrection.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5257,
            "text": "Do you feel secure that He who is in the heaven will not cause the earth to swallow you up while it shakes?",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5258,
            "text": "Do you feel secure that He who is in the heaven will not loose against you a squall of pebbles then you shall know how was My warning.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5259,
            "text": "Those who have gone before you also belied (their Messengers) then how was My disapproval!",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5260,
            "text": "Do they not observe the birds above them, spreading their wings and folding them? None, except the Merciful holds them. Surely, He sees all things.",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5261,
            "text": "Or, who is it that shall be your host to help you, other than the Merciful? Indeed, the unbelievers are only deluded.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5262,
            "text": "Or, who is it that shall provide for you if He withholds His provision? Yet they persist in arrogance and aversion.",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5263,
            "text": "What, is he who walks, falling upon his face, more guided than he who walks upright on a Straight Path!",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5264,
            "text": "Say: 'It is He who has created you and given to you hearing, sight and hearts but little is it that you thank'",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5265,
            "text": "Say: 'It was He who created you, dispersing you in the earth, and to Him you shall be gathered'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5266,
            "text": "They ask: 'When will this promise come, if you speak truthfully'",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5267,
            "text": "Say: 'The knowledge (of that) is with Allah; I am only a clear warner'",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 563,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5268,
            "text": "Then, when they see it drawing near, the faces of the unbelievers will be blackened, and it is said: 'This is what you were promised'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5269,
            "text": "Say: 'What do you think, if Allah destroys me and those with me, or has mercy upon us, who then will protect the unbelievers from the painful punishment'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5270,
            "text": "Say: 'He is the Merciful. In Him we believe and in Him we put all our trust. Indeed, you shall soon know who is in clear error'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5271,
            "text": "Say: 'What do you think. If your water should sink into the earth in the morning, who then would bring you running water'",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 497,
            "hizbQuarter": 225,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 68,
        "name": "سُورَةُ القَلَمِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Qalam",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Pen",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5272,
            "text": "Noon. By the Pen and that (the angels) write,",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5273,
            "text": "you are not, because of the favor of your Lord, mad.",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5274,
            "text": "Indeed, there is an unfailing wage for you.",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5275,
            "text": "Surely, you (Prophet Muhammad) are of a great morality.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5276,
            "text": "You shall see and they will see",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5277,
            "text": "which of you is the demented.",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5278,
            "text": "Indeed, your Lord knows very well those who strayed from His Path, and those who are guided.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5279,
            "text": "Therefore, do not obey those who belie,",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5280,
            "text": "they wish you would compromise, then, they would compromise.",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5281,
            "text": "And do not obey every mean swearer,",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5282,
            "text": "the backbiter who goes about slandering,",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5283,
            "text": "those who hinder good, the guilty aggressor,",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5284,
            "text": "the crude of low character",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5285,
            "text": "because he has wealth and sons.",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5286,
            "text": "When Our verses are recited to him, he says: 'They are but fairytales of the ancients'",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 564,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5287,
            "text": "We shall mark him upon his nose!",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5288,
            "text": "We have tried them as We tried the owners of the garden who had sworn that in the morning they would reap it,",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5289,
            "text": "without adding to their swearing, (Allah willing, InshaAllah).",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5290,
            "text": "Then, a visitation from your Lord came down upon it while they slept,",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5291,
            "text": "and in the morning it was if the garden had been reaped.",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5292,
            "text": "(Then) in the morning they called out to one another, saying:",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5293,
            "text": "'Come out to your tillage if you want to reap'",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5294,
            "text": "And so they departed, whispering to one another:",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5295,
            "text": "'No needy person shall set foot in it today'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5296,
            "text": "And they went out early, determined in their resolve.",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5297,
            "text": "But when they saw it they said: 'We have surely gone astray.",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5298,
            "text": "No, rather, we have been prevented'",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5299,
            "text": "(Whereupon) the best among them said: 'Did I not say to you to exalt (Allah)'",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5300,
            "text": "'Exaltations to Allah, our Lord' they said, 'We were truly harmdoers'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5301,
            "text": "And they came blaming one another.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5302,
            "text": "They said 'Woe to us, truly we were insolent'",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5303,
            "text": "It may be that our Lord will give us better than it in exchange. To our Lord we humbly turn'",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5304,
            "text": "Such was their punishment. But the punishment of the Everlasting Life is much greater, if they but knew.",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 498,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5305,
            "text": "Surely, the cautious shall have Gardens of Bliss with their Lord.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5306,
            "text": "What, shall We make those who are submissive like the wrongdoers?",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5307,
            "text": "What is the matter with you then, how do you judge?",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5308,
            "text": "Or, have you a Book from which you study",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5309,
            "text": "surely in it you shall have whatever you choose!",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5310,
            "text": "Or, have you an oath from Us that stretches to the Day of Resurrection (if so) you shall surely have what you judge!",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5311,
            "text": "Ask them, which of them will guarantee that!",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5312,
            "text": "Or, do they have associates? Then let them bring their associates, if what they say is true!",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5313,
            "text": "On the Day when the leg shall be bared, and they are ordered to prostrate themselves, they will be unable.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 565,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5314,
            "text": "Their eyes will be humbled, and humiliation shall spread over them for they were already ordered to prostrate themselves when they were undiminished.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5315,
            "text": "Therefore, leave Me with he who belied this discourse. We will draw them on little by little from where they do not know.",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5316,
            "text": "I shall respite them, My stratagem is firm.",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5317,
            "text": "Or, do you ask them for a wage, so that they are burdened withdebt?",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5318,
            "text": "Or, is the Unseen with them, and they are writing it down!",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5319,
            "text": "So be patient with the judgement of your Lord and do not be like the Companion of the Whale (Jonah), when he called out choking inwardly.",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5320,
            "text": "Had the favor of his Lord not come upon him, he would have been blamed, cast upon the shore.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5321,
            "text": "But his Lord had chosen him and He placed him among the righteous.",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5322,
            "text": "When the unbelievers hear the Reminder, they nearly strike you down with their glances, and say: 'Surely, he is mad'",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5323,
            "text": "But it is nothing other than a Reminder for all the worlds.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 499,
            "hizbQuarter": 226,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "number": 69,
        "name": "سُورَةُ الحَاقَّةِ",
        "englishName": "Al-Haaqqa",
        "englishNameTranslation": "The Reality",
        "revelationType": "Meccan",
        "ayahs": [
          {
            "number": 5324,
            "text": "The Resurrection Verifier;",
            "numberInSurah": 1,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5325,
            "text": "and what is the Resurrection Verifier?",
            "numberInSurah": 2,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5326,
            "text": "What makes you to know what the Resurrection Verifier is?",
            "numberInSurah": 3,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5327,
            "text": "Thamood and Aad belied the Clatterer.",
            "numberInSurah": 4,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5328,
            "text": "Thamood, they were destroyed by the violent shout (of Gabriel),",
            "numberInSurah": 5,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5329,
            "text": "as for Aad, they were destroyed by a howling, violent wind",
            "numberInSurah": 6,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5330,
            "text": "that He subjected upon them for seven nights and eight days consecutively and you might have seen them struck down as if they were the stumps of palm trees that had fallen down.",
            "numberInSurah": 7,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5331,
            "text": "Can you see any remnant of them now?",
            "numberInSurah": 8,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 566,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5332,
            "text": "Similarly, Pharaoh, and those before him, and the ruined villages, sinned",
            "numberInSurah": 9,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5333,
            "text": "and rebelled against their Lord's Messenger. So He took them with a stern taking.",
            "numberInSurah": 10,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5334,
            "text": "And when the waters rose (high) We carried you in the sailing (Ark),",
            "numberInSurah": 11,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5335,
            "text": "making it a Reminder for you, for all attentive ears to retain.",
            "numberInSurah": 12,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5336,
            "text": "When a single blow is blown on the Horn,",
            "numberInSurah": 13,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5337,
            "text": "when the earth with all its mountains is lifted up and crushed with a single blow,",
            "numberInSurah": 14,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5338,
            "text": "on that Day, the Event occurs.",
            "numberInSurah": 15,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5339,
            "text": "The heaven will be split; because on that Day it will be frail.",
            "numberInSurah": 16,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5340,
            "text": "The angels will stand on all its sides. And on that Day, eight (of them) will carry the Throne of your Lord above them.",
            "numberInSurah": 17,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5341,
            "text": "On that Day you shall be exposed, and no secret of yours will remain hidden.",
            "numberInSurah": 18,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5342,
            "text": "Then, he who is given his book in his right hand will say: 'Here, take and read my book!",
            "numberInSurah": 19,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5343,
            "text": "Indeed, I knew that I should come to my reckoning'",
            "numberInSurah": 20,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5344,
            "text": "His shall be a pleasing life",
            "numberInSurah": 21,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5345,
            "text": "in a high Garden,",
            "numberInSurah": 22,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5346,
            "text": "its fruits are near.",
            "numberInSurah": 23,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5347,
            "text": "(It will be said): 'Eat and drink with a good appetite because of what you did in days long passed'",
            "numberInSurah": 24,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5348,
            "text": "But, he who is given his book in his left hand will say: 'Woe to me, would that my book had not been given to me!",
            "numberInSurah": 25,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5349,
            "text": "Nor that I knew my reckoning!",
            "numberInSurah": 26,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5350,
            "text": "Would that it (my death) had ended it all!",
            "numberInSurah": 27,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5351,
            "text": "My wealth has not helped me a thing",
            "numberInSurah": 28,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5352,
            "text": "and my authority has been destroyed'",
            "numberInSurah": 29,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5353,
            "text": "(It will be said): 'Take him and bind him.",
            "numberInSurah": 30,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5354,
            "text": "Roast him in Hell,",
            "numberInSurah": 31,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5355,
            "text": "then in a chain seventy arm's lengths long insert him.",
            "numberInSurah": 32,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5356,
            "text": "He did not believe in Allah, the Great,",
            "numberInSurah": 33,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5357,
            "text": "nor did he urge the feeding of the needy.",
            "numberInSurah": 34,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 567,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5358,
            "text": "Today he shall have no loyal friend here,",
            "numberInSurah": 35,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5359,
            "text": "nor any food except foul pus",
            "numberInSurah": 36,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5360,
            "text": "that none but sinners eat'",
            "numberInSurah": 37,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 500,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5361,
            "text": "I swear by all that you can see,",
            "numberInSurah": 38,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5362,
            "text": "and all that you do not see,",
            "numberInSurah": 39,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5363,
            "text": "that this is the speech of a noble Messenger.",
            "numberInSurah": 40,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5364,
            "text": "It is not the speech of a poet little do you believe",
            "numberInSurah": 41,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5365,
            "text": "nor is it the speech of a soothsayer little do you remember.",
            "numberInSurah": 42,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5366,
            "text": "(It is) a sending down from the Lord of all the Worlds.",
            "numberInSurah": 43,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5367,
            "text": "Had he invented sayings against Us,",
            "numberInSurah": 44,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5368,
            "text": "We would have seized him by the right hand",
            "numberInSurah": 45,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5369,
            "text": "then, We would surely have cut from him the aorta (vein)",
            "numberInSurah": 46,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5370,
            "text": "not one of you could have prevented it from him.",
            "numberInSurah": 47,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5371,
            "text": "Indeed, it is a Reminder to those who fear Allah,",
            "numberInSurah": 48,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5372,
            "text": "We know that there are some among you who will belie.",
            "numberInSurah": 49,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5373,
            "text": "Indeed, it is a sorrow to the unbelievers",
            "numberInSurah": 50,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5374,
            "text": "yet it is a certain truth.",
            "numberInSurah": 51,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          },
          {
            "number": 5375,
            "text": "Exalt the Name of your Lord, the Great.",
            "numberInSurah": 52,
            "juz": 29,
            "manzil": 7,
            "page": 568,
            "ruku": 501,
            "hizbQuarter": 227,
            "sajda": false
          }
        ]
